description.narrative: (Tanzania): Project objectives are to improve the health status of Tanzanians by expanding the impact of targeted social marketing initiatives aligned to measurable behavioral outcomes in HIV/AIDS, family planning, reproductive health, child survival, malaria, and strengthening local capacity to sustain social marketing health activities. Activities are focused in Dar es Salaam, Dodoma, Mwanza, Arusha, Shinyanga, Mara, Manyara, and Mbeya. The project supports both the Government of Tanzania and the U.S. Government health priorities including the Global Health Initiative Strategy by increasing uptake of preventive health services and product use. Major activities include strengthening and expanding demand, access and supply of essential health commodities including oral contraceptives (OCs) to large percentages of the Tanzanian population. TSMP will strengthen research to measure willingness to pay for various commodities such as OCs and increase support to the public sector to improve condom programming. This activity has, and will continue to, result in increased access to essential health commodities for improved health outcomes
